content_chunks.content: This digital course is designed to provide knowledge and practical experience in 3 levels (basic, intermediate, and advanced) to learn the calculation methods of composite structures under different effects and in the cases of rigid and flexible connection between layers. The course provides information to recognize and analyse problems related to the design of composite structures, apply advanced methods, and make rational structural decisions. Additionally, the course focuses on combining different eco-friendly materials in composite structures using the best mechanical properties and reducing the amount of materials that cause the highest foot print of CO2.

Composite structures design technology for sustainable construction and CO₂ footprint reduction - this course delivers comprehensive expertise in calculating and designing eco-friendly composite structures that optimize mechanical properties while minimizing environmental impact. Students master layer interaction analysis, stress-strain evaluation methods, and partial stiffness calculations for both rigid and flexible layer connections in structural systems. The curriculum covers lightweight composite design, sandwich panel engineering, steel-concrete composite structures, and stiffening element optimization that enable sustainable building solutions. Graduates emerge skilled in implementing eco-friendly material combinations, structural decision optimization, and advanced composite calculation methodologies that reduce CO₂ emissions while maintaining superior structural performance through innovative material engineering and sustainable design principles.

content_chunks.title: The essence of composite structures, advantages, areas of use, classification, and their types

General properties of composite structures, their requirements, and interaction between layers. Behaviour of composite structures under the influence of external loads. Stress and strain state in composite structures
Calculation principles of composite structures with rigid layers. Layer reduction method. Calculation of structures by evaluating the deformation properties of individual layers
Calculation of flexural members with rigid thick layers (considering the deformation of individual layers and using the reduction method)
Calculation principles of composite structures by estimating the partial stiffness of the connection between layers
Calculation of composite structures by estimating the partial stiffness of the connection between layers
Calculation principles of light weight composite structures
Calculation of lightweight composite structures with stiffening elements
Calculation principles of steel-concrete composite structures
Calculation of compressive and flexural composite structures with a thin outer steel layer
